== 8. O-O ==
White castles their king to safety to unpin the knight and to start preparing e4.

Black can now choose to either play '''[[/8...Nbd7/]]''' or '''[[/8...O-O/]]'''. Play is very likely to transpose, but different deviations from the main line are possible depending on which move Black plays first. The main difference is that after 8...O-O, Black has many possibilities of fully preventing e4, while after 8...Nbd7 trying to do so is more dangerous for Black.

In both positions, White is likely to play Qe2, preparing e4. There is, however, another option.

=== Chasing the bishop ===
It is not uncommon for White to play an early Nh4, chasing away the bishop. This option is most effective if White hasn't played 9. Qe2 yet, so that Qc2 can be played while gaining a tempo on the pawn.

